reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's unreal how expensive everything has gotten. I was not willing to pay as much as I did but I needed a cabinet for my canned goods and other non-perishable foods.This one works great. The color is also very nice.It's not solid wood, it's compressed wood. One of the boards was cracked at the top but we worked around it.Once put together, we couldn't see the crack.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Organizational Bliss - ClosetMaid Pantry Cabinet Elevates Your Storage Game

It adds a touch of elegance to the space while remaining highly functional.**3. Sturdy Build:** The cabinet is built to last. It's constructed with quality materials that feel robust and durable. I'm confident it will serve me well for years to come.**4. Easy Assembly:** Putting this cabinet together was a relatively straightforward process. They allow me to create storage spaces tailored to my needs. It's versatile enough to hold everything from tall bottles to small kitchen gadgets.**6. Two Doors for Concealment:** The two doors provide a neat and tidy appearance, keeping my kitchen essentials hidden from view. It's a great option for maintaining a clutter-free look.**7. Versatile Usage:** While I primarily use it as a kitchen pantry, this cabinet's design and functionality make it suitable for laundry rooms, utility rooms, or even as extra storage in the garage.**8. Affordable:** Considering the quality and the storage capacity it offers, the price of this pantry cabinet is budget-friendly. It's an excellent investment for anyone looking to enhance their home organization.In conclusion, the ClosetMaid Pantry Cabinet with 2 Doors has exceeded my expectations. It's an organizational powerhouse that combines style with functionality. Whether you're looking to declutter your kitchen, laundry room, or utility space, this cabinet is a reliable solution. It's an attractive, sturdy, and versatile piece of furniture that makes storage a pleasure. I highly recommend it to anyone in need of an elegant storage solution for their home.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I have assembled many furniture pieces (and I hate it!) I think this cabinet had the easiest instructions ever. My only complaint about assembly is none of the pieces were labeled but I’m being a stickler because regardless it was easy. It was insanely heavy and once it was assembled I had to call someone to help me get it upright.Overall it looks good but the door handles are very low on it and I think it looks weird plus they are plastic handles. I am going to wallpaper the cabinet and bring the new handles I bought higher.One more thing I need to mention is this cabinet MUST BE ANCHORED TO THE WALL or it might tip and as I mentioned it’s extremely heavy. The backing is cardboard so you won’t be anchoring it thru that. I had to order separate wall anchors for this because I can’t do it thru the top because of where I’m placing it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really good unit!
reviews.reviewText: I got this shelf just yesterday and set it up on my own in just a couple of hours. It’s so easy to put together! I went a little different than what the instructions said due to lack of work space, but even then it was so easy to tell what to do and then easy to do it. I really liked that it used normal screws and nails because it really helps hold it together. Guide holes were a bonus! My only real issue with it was how easy it was to tip over, but it came with a piece to attach between the unit and the wall in order to prevent tipping, so great planning on the manufacturer’s part. So definitely use that piece. I’d also love if it had a couple more shelves to put inside, but that’s personal preference lol. But yes, overall it’s wonderful! I would definitely recommend it to anyone who asked.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: This arrived yesterday and I put it together this morning. I could kick myself for not wiping down each piece and inspecting it before putting it together. The way it goes together requires you to put the doors on the floor and build it up from there, which is different from any other I've ever built. As a result, there were some things I didn't even notice until I put it together. I stood it up and started wiping it down with a dust cloth, but many of the spots I thought were dust and packaging turned out to be scratches, some of them big, all over the front doors. It was built on a special wool covering that I use when building furniture just to make sure I don't scratch anything, so I know it wasn't me. Then when I wiped down one of the sides, close to the bottom I noticed a huge scratch going all the way across. When I got close to it I realized it was more than just a scratch; it was a crack in the particle board all the way across it!! I never even saw it. That was the side that attached to the doors first and the way it was facing, I wasn't looking at that side. So now I have this thing put together that not only looks bad, but is structurally unsound. I tried clicking on the link they have to contact ClosetMaid if we have any issue, but each time I've tried, I get the message that it can't be found. I'm not even sure what to do at this point. The box was thrown out this morning and it is put together, so how can I even return it to Amazon? I will try to add pics or video to this review. UPDATE: Amazon Customer Service made it right for me.

UPDATE: company was willing to reimburse me at 15%..that really doesnt cover the damaged For some reason I did not recieve notification this product was being delivered. Once I opened the box I noticed the pieces were damages. Although it was easy to assemble and instructions were clear, it is not worth the $$$. Not to mention that it is damaged in a few spots.

I would not recommend this product. It is cheaply made with a cardboard backing piece that is barely big enough to fasten to the back. It is very tippy so would not be suitable for a free standing pantry. Not happy with the product but 24" units are hard to find.

reviews.reviewTitle: I ordered it and I didn’t read the size it’s far too small

And it came with absolutely no hardware or instructions (I used my own to try make it work). I wish I would've taken more photos before asking for a refund and throwing everything away.
